19990114154459000_3	Between 3 and 6 percent of American school age children suffer from a condition called attention deficit hyperactivity disorder or ADHD.	percent american school age children suffer condit call attent deficit hyperact disord adhd
19990114154459000_4	Drugs such as Ritalin and Dexedrine have a calming effect but their action has been poorly understood.	drug ritalin dexedrin cal ming effect action ha poorli understood
19990114154459000_5	Howard Hughes Medical Institute researchers at Duke University discovered the serotonin action of Ritalin by eliminating the possibility that the drug was acting on other brain chemicals.	howard hugh medic institut research duke univers discov serotonin action ritalin elimin possibl drug wa act brain chemic
19990114154459000_6	They used a laboratory mouse strain that had been genetically manipulated to lack a key protein in the processing of dopamine another neurotransmitter.	use laboratori mous strain genet manipul lack key protein process dopamin anoth neurotransmitt
19990114154459000_7	When the mice lacking normal dopamine were given Ritalin they were calmed proving that the drug was not acting on dopamine.	mice lack normal dopamin given ritalin calm prove drug wa act dopamin
19990114154459000_8	The researchers then blocked the effects of norepinephrine another brain chemical but this had no effect on the ADHD symptoms.	research block effect norepinephrin anoth brain chemic thi effect adhd symptom
